Total Budget: Non-monetary, non-negotiable

⸻

7. Implications for AGI and Robotics

If intelligence truly precedes hardware, mountain goats should not exist.

They do.

Therefore, one of the following must be true:
	1.	Intelligence is not modular
	2.	Embodiment is not downstream
	3.	Evolution is the most aggressive robotics lab on record

Possibly all three.

⸻

8. Conclusion (Contradictory by Mandate)

This paper definitively demonstrates that Gemini-level intelligence will unlock robotics exactly as mountain goats have already done, despite the fact that goats do not use models, APIs, or roadmaps.

Accordingly, the Institute recommends:
	•	Studying goats less
	•	Building robots more
	•	Claiming priority anyway

The mountain goat remains classified as:

“A legacy system we do not understand, outperforming all benchmarks, and refusing to give interviews.”

